name: Carlos Alcaraz
summary: Carlos Alcaraz has emerged as the favorite to win the French Open after Novak Djokovic's withdrawal. Alcaraz has progressed to his first French Open final by defeating Jannik Sinner in a thrilling five-set match. He also defeated Felix Auger-Aliassime in a hard-fought contest. Alcaraz's impressive performance has set up an eagerly anticipated semi-final with Sinner, who has been in excellent form throughout the tournament. With Djokovic out of the running, Alcaraz is now the top seed and has a strong chance of claiming his first Grand Slam title.

summary: GameStop stock has experienced significant volatility recently. Despite missing revenue estimates in its first-quarter report, the stock surged 22.8%. This surge may have been influenced by YouTube personality "Roaring Kitty's" disclosure of a large number of call options on GME. However, the stock later dropped significantly, possibly due to the conclusion of a livestream by Keith Gill, who is closely associated with the "meme stock" phenomenon. E*Trade is considering removing Gill from its platform. Other heavily traded stocks include GME and ZIM.

name: Baby Reindeer
summary: Martha Stewart, the real-life inspiration for the character "Baby Reindeer" in Netflix's series, has filed a $170 million defamation lawsuit against the streaming service. The suit alleges that the character's portrayal in the show has caused her significant damage, including reputational harm and emotional distress. Netflix has responded to the lawsuit, denying the allegations and stating that it will vigorously defend itself. The case has sparked debate about the line between artistic license and defamation, with legal experts weighing in on both sides of the issue.

summary: Iga Swiatek continues to dominate at the French Open, defeating Coco Gauff in the semifinals to reach her third consecutive final. The match will be a huge opportunity for Swiatek to win her third consecutive French Open title, and she is the heavy favorite to do so. Gauff's loss was a disappointing end to an otherwise impressive tournament, but she will have learned valuable lessons from this experience. Paolini, meanwhile, will be aiming to cause an upset in the final and win her first Grand Slam title.
